verbose_text: Also, over-expression of miR-433 increased the proliferation of cardiac fibroblasts and promoted their differentiation into myofibroblasts, whereas knockdown of miR-433 suppressed these responses upon transforming growth factor-beta (TGF-beta) or Angiotensin II (Ang II) stimulation.
